---
import Header from "../components/header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/footer.astro";
import Aside from "../components/aside.astro";
import CodeCard from "../components/codecard.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
		<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Abril+Fatface&family=Merriweather:ital,opsz,wght@0,18..144,300..900;1,18..144,300..900&family=Montserrat:ital,wght@0,100..900;1,100..900&family=Nunito:ital,wght@0,200..1000;1,200..1000&family=Poppins:ital,wght@0,100;0,200;0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;0,800;0,900;1,100;1,200;1,300;1,400;1,500;1,600;1,700;1,800;1,900&family=Space+Mono:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400;1,700&family=Work+Sans:wght@300&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
		<title>Home - Bash Programming by Bruno Victoria</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<input type="checkbox" id="toggle-menu" hidden>
        <Header showMenu={true} showLogo={false} />
		<Aside />
		<main>
			<section class="home-section">
				<!-- Hero Section -->
				<div class="hero-section">
					<img src="/linux-pic.png" alt="Linux Logo" class="profile-picture">
					<h1>Welcome to Bash Programming</h1>
					<p class="hero-subtitle">Learn Linux commands and bash scripting from the ground up</p>
					<p class="hero-description">Hi! I'm <strong>Bruno Victoria</strong>, and I'm here to help you with the command line. Whether you're a complete beginner or looking to sharpen your skills, this site offers information and examples to help you</p>
				</div>

				<!-- What You'll Learn Section -->
				<div class="learning-section">
					<h2>What You'll Learn</h2>
					<div class="learning-grid">
						<div class="learning-card">
							<h3>🚀 Essential Commands</h3>
							<p>Master the fundamental Linux/bash commands every developer needs to know.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="learning-card">
							<h3>📝 Script Writing</h3>
							<p>Write your first bash scripts and automate repetitive tasks.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="learning-card">
							<h3>🔧 File Management</h3>
							<p>Navigate the filesystem, manage files, and understand permissions.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="learning-card">
							<h3>⚡ Productivity Tips</h3>
							<p>Keyboard shortcuts, aliases, and tricks to work faster in the terminal.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Quick Start Section -->
				<div class="quickstart-section">
					<h2>Quick Start</h2>
					<p>New to the command line? Try these essential commands to get started:</p>
					<CodeCard 
						command={['pwd', 'ls', 'whoami', 'echo "Hello, Linux!"']}
						output={['/home/user', 'Documents Downloads Pictures Videos', 'user', 'Hello, Linux!']}
					/>
					<p>These commands show you where you are (<span class="bash-term">pwd</span>), what's in your current folder (<span class="bash-term">ls</span>), who you're logged in as (<span class="bash-term">whoami</span>), and how to print text (<span class="bash-term">echo</span>).</p>
				</div>
				<!-- Why Learn Bash Section -->
				<div class="why-section">
					<h2>Why Learn Bash?</h2>
					<div class="why-grid">
						<div class="why-item">
							<h4>🔄 Automation</h4>
							<p>Automate repetitive tasks and save hours of manual work.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="why-item">
							<h4>💻 Server Management</h4>
							<p>Manage servers, deploy applications, and troubleshoot issues.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="why-item">
							<h4>🔗 Tool Integration</h4>
							<p>Connect different tools and create powerful workflows.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="why-item">
							<h4>📊 Data Processing</h4>
							<p>Process and analyze text files and data efficiently.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Call to Action -->
				<div class="cta-section">
					<h2>Ready to Get Started?</h2>
					<p>Jump into your first lesson and start your bash journey today!</p>
					<div class="cta-buttons">
						<a href="/intro" class="cta-button primary">Start Learning</a>
						<a href="/contact" class="cta-button secondary">Get in Touch</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
